# Application Blueprint

When generating or refactoring, preserve this architecture:
- Next.js App Router in `src/app`
- Domain route groups: home, classes, students, appointments
- Domain-local `_actions` and `_components`
- Prisma/Postgres with schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`
- JWT cookie sessions via `src/app/lib/session.ts`
- Shared domain types and Zod form contracts in `src/app/lib/definitions.ts`; pure grading/behavior logic in `src/app/lib/grading.ts`
- Global modal shell: `ModalProvider` + `<Modal />` in root `layout.tsx`, context in `src/app/(_home)/_context/Modal.tsx`, triggers under `OpenModalComponents`

Implementation order:
1. Structure folders
2. Define DB models and relations
3. Build auth/session pipeline
4. Add server actions per domain
5. Build components
6. Assemble pages/layouts
